reviewText: When I took my kids to see this in the theater, it was pretty empty.  And I'm sure I was the only one really laughing throughout.  That's when I got that Good Burger was made more for people my age than theirs.  As they've gotten older, they've come to appreciate it more.I know it was an expansion of an All That skit, but it had one big difference.  On All That, the Good Burger skit was mostly about Ed, played by Kel Mitchell, and his goofy talk and attitude.  This movie also had Kenan Thompson, as Dexter.  That made all the difference, because Dexter actually had a story.  Ed is funny, innocent, and what not, but he didn't bring the story by himself.So, I'm watching this movie, wondering how Dexter's going to get out of his problem, when everyone somehow ends up in a mental institution.  And who's in the middle of the scene, but George Clinton, turning the dial on the radio to Knee Deep--one of my favorite songs of all time!  And when Kel leads the room in a rendition of the Thriller dance, I knew I'd found one of my new favorite movies.Kenan and Kel, George Clinton, Sinbad as a tacky, over-the-top 70s jive talking teacher--this movie was hilarious!  And it's definitely one of the 7 happiest black movies of all time.
Title: Good Burger VHS

reviewText: This is an underrated movie that never gets old.  Kenan and Kel play Dexter, an irratable high school student in debt, and Ed, a dim-witted but lovable dude who loves his job a little too much.  They are a sort of reverse Abbott and Costello.  The two must save Good Burger from Mondo Burger, a Dave and Busters-esque new restaurant across the street and its successful but cruel manager Kurt, who always refers to himself in the third person.  Along the way, they both learn a thing or two about being friends and partners.

reviewText: Being a person who loves both kid and family films, I purchased this movie from Suncoast Video in Livingston Mall.  After having left the mall, however, I did have my initial misgivings.  Would it live up to the "Good Burger" sketches that were regularly performed on Nickelodeon's tween version of "In Living Color"?I'm happy--deliriously happy, I might add--to say that this movie did not disappoint.  I even showed it to my niece the next time she was over our house for a visit, and she and I laughed throughout the whole movie.  Kids' movies aren't like this anymore; if anything, the kids are smart-mouthed, irreverent, and disrespectful.  And they even managed to include a little moral:  that wealth and power aren't the things that will sustain.  Ultimately, doing a good job and selling a good product ("good burger") and keeping your customers happy will prove itself in the end.
summary: Crazy, messy fun for the whole family!!!!

reviewText: Who would have thought Kel Mitchell and Kenan Thompson could pull it off? Just thinking about it sends up a lot of red flags doesn't it? Sure, there slapstick style comedy works well on Nickelodeon but that's television.  A half hour of funny on the T.V. screen can turn into 95 minutes of pure stupidity and torture when stretched into a full length motion picture if it's not done correctly.Believe it or not, `Good Burger' was done absolutely to perfection (pun intended). Kenan and Kel star as Dexter and Ed, two high school kids working at the local fast-food restaurant known as, Good Burger. Yes, the movie contains loads of the over-the-top physical comedy the two are known for, but it also boasts a very inventive, well thought out script containing lots of quotable lines, a strong storyline and a great supporting cast that keeps your interest peaked from beginning to end.Your children will love it and so will you!
summary: "Not To Your Knowledge"  ~  Kenan & Kel Discover the Secret Sauce to Success

reviewText: Oh, Good Burger. A product of the 90's in every sense. It's got Kenan and Kel, it's got Less Than Jake, it's got Sinbad, it's got Carmen Electra in an auspicious near-debut, and it's got Abe Vigoda at the peak of his abilities. It's also a product of Nickelodeon in their peak years. Good Burger is stupidly funny, but it's not stupid to the point where the audience loses interest. It has a surprisingly compelling story and a lot of energy to carry it to it's wild finale. It's about as guilty as guilty pleasures get, but for anyone who enjoyed the film as a child and wants to revisit it, it holds up shockingly well. P.S. Imagine if Spike Lee had directed Good Burger. It probably would have been hailed as his best film since Do The Right Thing.

reviewText: I am outraged that this movie was passed up for an Academy Award.  Instead movies like Titanic, and Braveheart are snatching the Oscars like butter, and movies like Good Burger and The Power Rangers are left in the dust.  Not since Lucielle Ball have I seen comedy like these two young actors,  Kenan and Kel.  They're the Abbott and Costello of the 90's.  When I saw  this movie, I laughed and cried.  The emotional roller coaster Good Burger  takes you on is rivaled only by The Green Mile.  I can't say enough good  things about this masterpiece on film.  If you could frame a movie and put  it next to the Mona Lisa this would be the one.  Don't let this gem of a  film escape your clutches.  BUY IT NOW!

reviewText: Based on The Popular Skit on Nickelodeon's ''All That'', ''Good Burger'' Follows The Histarical Adventures of Friends Dexter and Ed, Who Work at The Famous Fast-Food Restruant, Good Burger. One Day, a Brand New Fast-Food Restruant, Mondo Burger, Opens Across The Street of Good Burger, in which is Trying To Put Good Burger Out of Buisness. Shortly After Figuring Out Mondo Burger Makes Thier Big Burger Meat Patties Out of Ileagal Supstences, Dexter and Ed Start Out on a Mission To Prove Mondo Burger Guilty as Charged.Though I Haven't Seen Much of the ''Good Burger'' Skit on Nickelodeon's Show ''All That'', But I Can Tell You, GOOD BURGER The Movie is One of The Best Kids Films Ever Made, and Not Only is it Funny For Kids, it's Funny For Teens and Adults if Thay Happen To Be Caught in The Right Mood To Watch Such A Film. Nickelodeon's Films That Are Based on Thier Shows/Skits, Thay Don't Live Up To What Thier Show/Skit Was, or Sometimes It's Just Not Good at All, But ''Good Burger'' Lives Up To Fans of The Skit. Kenan Thompson, Kel Mitchell and Everybody Who Were in This Film, Played Them Great and Histracally Funny. It's So Hard Finding a Good Kids Film That Doesn't Show any Thing So Violent, or Sexual (Even Though GOOD BURGER Gets it's PG Rating For Some Sex-Related Humor), or Language So Mild and Mean You Would Turn off Your TV or Walking Out of The Theater. GOOD BURGER is Nice, Good Fun For The Family. I Highly Recommend Everyone Watches GOOD BURGER.Also recommended For Fans of GOOD BURGER:SpongeBob SquarePants - The Complete 1st SeasonThe SpongeBob SquarePants MovieBig Fat LiarThe Amanda Show, Vol. 1 - Amanda, Please / The Amanda Show, Vol. 2 - The Girls' RoomAnimaniacs, Vol. 1-3THERE ARE NO SPECIAL FEATURES ON THIS DVDBut, Thay Could've Put at Least a trailer or a Making-of Feature.Overall RatingsMovie-5/5DVD-1.5/5

reviewText: Kenan Thompson and Kel Mitchell do a good job in this flick. This is definitely a film inspired from the 'All That' tv show on Nickelodeon (back when 'All That' was actually a good show) It will definitely come across as cheesy to some people, but this is a movie you want to watch with a light heart and open mind.Kel Mitchell is often cast as a stupid character in 'All That', and it happens again here. I don't know what Kel thinks about that personally, but he plays the character well here. He is even depicted as taking a shower in his Good Burger uniform.He and Kenan's character play a pair of employees at Good Burger, and the main conflict in this film is a rival burger place setting up shop with giant burger patties, threatening to drive Good Burger out of business. Slapstick comedy ensues as Good Burger tries to deal with its competitor while trying to find the secret to its success. If you like Kenan and Kel on 'All That' or 'Kenan & Kel', then you're bound to like them in this movie as well.

reviewText: I was 7 years old when this came out, and I've loved it ever since because I was a big fan of All That and the Kenan & Kel show. Kenan & Kel do an awesome job and are the perfect partners. Mondo Burger is opening right across the street from Good Burger. It literally puts Good Burger out of business. When Dexter tastes Ed's sauce for burgers, they open to the public, and they get the customers back. Soon, the manager at Mondo Burger named Kurt tries to steal Ed's recipe. Soon, they poison the sauce and send Ed and Dexter, and Otis to Demented Hills. They have until 10:00 in the morning to stop everyone from eating a Good Burger. Will they stop them in time and stop Mondo Burger? I highly recommend GOOD BURGER!!!

reviewText: Yes, the film does have the "slime factor" so prevalent in Nickelodeon's productions.Yes, the film has jokes that only a seven-year-old could love.Yes, the film features Sinbad and Abe Vigoda in supporting roles as "adults" that are the brunt of youngsters antics.Yes, the film has a likeable character with the intelligence of a cucumber and a genuine innocence that endears him to all.But, it is a delightful little movie that appeals to a cross-section of the audience in a time when there are few genuine non-offensive family films.And, it does have one really cool dance number to "Knee Deep" featuring the funk man himself, George Clinton.
summary: A Little Bit of Juvenile Humor Goes a Long Way

reviewText: There are very few movies that make me fall off my chair and giggle profusely. This is one of them. I don't know why I giggle so much at this ridiculous movie. It is so silly. Yeah, so... so... silly. But I find it so, so charming.But why? There are so many ridiculous puns. There is nothing on this blue and green Earth that I like more than puns and this movie provides them either intentionally or unintentionally. SAUCE!!! etc... I cab;t think of many of them now because I am still chuckling from the after-effects of this deleightful film.It is just absurd beyond comparison, well every single film about teenagers with a PG rating would be, but unlike many other films, the toned down language and situations of this film provide it with additional pun fodder and additional charm. The formulaic story and the formulaic characters are all groovy with me.I am not even high or drunk, but this movie intoxicates me with a bizarre laughter. Kenan and Kel have made me happy today. BRILLIANT!
